\f1\b \cf2 \cb3 \
Reporting hate crimes
\f0\b0 \cf0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Law enforcement should build trust with those they serve to increase the willingness among victims and their communities to report hate crimes, said Arusha Gordon, associate director of the James Byrd Jr. Center to Stop Hate, a project of the Lawyer\'92s Committee for Civil Rights Under Law.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
Trust may erode if victims and their communities feel that law enforcement won\'92t properly address reported incidents, including hate crimes and hate bias incidents \'96 which don\'92t warrant criminal charges.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
Maryland police {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.mcac.maryland.gov/resources/2019%20Hate%20Bias%20Report.pdf"}}{\fldrslt \cf5 reported}} that, between 2017 and 2019, they were able to verify a lower percentage of race-, ethnicity- and ancestry-motivated hate bias incidents each year, even though the volume of such crimes increased over that span.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
The report defined a verified incident as one in which police confirmed a victim\'92s claim that bias contributed in whole, or in part, to the perpetrator\'92s actions.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
In 2017, Maryland police reported verifying 45% of race-, ethnicity- and ancestry-motivated hate bias incidents that victims reported.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
In 2018, police verified 24%; in 2019, that figure was 22%.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 None of the 11 anti-Asian hate bias incidents in 2019 were verified.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
Of the nine anti-white hate bias incidents that year, five were verified.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
\'93More people reported what they felt were incidents related to hate/bias,\'94 a Maryland State Police Department spokesperson said to Capital News Service in an email. \'93Police looked into those complaints, but the evidence was not there to \'91verify\'92 the incident as an actual hate/bias incident.\'94\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
It is difficult to prove that a perpetrator acted with bias, for example, if police aren\'92t able to locate and question that perpetrator, Marc Limansky, public information officer for the Anne Arundel County Police Department, said.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 Sen. Susan Lee, D-Montgomery, said that, while Shen, the community leader in Rockville, was courageous in reporting the recent attacks on her house to police, other victims of hate crimes or hate bias incidents may be hesitant to report such incidents.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
First generation immigrants who fled oppressive regimes may be skeptical of police, and other victims may be afraid to report their incident for fear of retaliation, said Lee, who is chair emeritus and founder of the Maryland Legislature\'92s Asian American and Pacific Islander caucus.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
Fear of retaliation is especially prevalent during the pandemic, which has reignited an anti-Asian flame that some leaders have fanned.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
Robert Redfield, adviser to Hogan and former director of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, said in a March interview with CNN\'92s Sanjay Gupta that he believes the virus originated in a Wuhan lab \'96 a theory that the World Health Organization previously {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.npr.org/2021/03/31/983156340/theory-that-covid-came-from-a-chinese-lab-takes-on-new-life-in-wake-of-who-repor"}}{\fldrslt \cf5 investigated}} and determined to be \'93extremely unlikely.\'94\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
Redfield\'92s comments drew swift condemnation from state officials, including Lee.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
\'93Words matter and are dangerous when they manifest themselves or provoke violent action against an entire ethnic group,\'94 Lee said in a press release denouncing Redfield\'92s comments. \'93Asian Americans and people from communities of color and all backgrounds all too well understand this \'96 and have lived this.\'94\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
The granddaughter of a Chinese immigrant, Lee still remembers the names of those who bullied her in middle and high school.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 She said that she was the daily target of racist remarks and other attacks, which she was too ashamed to tell her parents about at the time.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
Perhaps no figure validated anti-Asian hate moreso than former President Donald Trump, Lee said.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
With his racist references to the coronavirus as the \'93kung flu\'94 and \'93China virus,\'94 Trump emboldened people to express their prejudice, and he put a target on the backs of Asian Americans and Pacific Islanders, Lee said.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
Numerous attacks on Asian Americans that have made national headlines \'96 among them the rampage at three Atlanta-area spas in which a man killed eight people, including six women of Asian descent \'96 have caused Lee to be more vigilant when in public.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
\'93I don\'92t know if I\'92m going to be the next victim of a dangerous, vicious attack,\'94 Lee said.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
She has also urged her mother to be careful when in public \'96 even in her own neighborhood.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
When hate crime perpetrators target someone, they are sending a message to the entire demographic that the victim represents, and Gordon \'96 from the Lawyers\'92 Committee \'96 said that law enforcement must offset this message.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
The Maryland police and correctional training commissions, which the state Legislature established in 2016 to govern police certification and training, mandates that entry-level and in-service training among state, county and municipal law enforcement provide {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://mdle.net/regs/PSA_Police_Training_and_Standards_Comm.pdf"}}{\fldrslt \cf5 \'93special training, attention to and study of\'94}} hate crimes laws, including responding to and reporting incidents.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
The commission, however, leaves to each department the specifics of this training and doesn\'92t oversee how individual departments respond to reported hate crimes, Executive Director Albert Liebno said.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
In coordination with community leaders and organizations, law enforcement bodies should periodically evaluate the effectiveness of hate crime response training, according to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.theiacp.org/sites/default/files/2019-04/IACP_Hate%20Crimes_Action%20Agenda.pdf"}}{\fldrslt \cf5 recommendations}} that the International Association of Chiefs of Police and the Lawyers\'92 Committee published in 2019.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 Gov. Larry Hogan, R, whose wife, Yumi, was born in Korea, announced on April 9 the formation of a statewide workgroup that will create recommendations for improving the state\'92s response.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
Robert Hur, the state\'92s former top federal prosecutor and a Korean American, will head the workgroup, and Hogan plans to announce the other members in May.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
Jimmy Rhee, special secretary of the governor\'92s office of small, minority and women business affairs and a member of Hogan\'92s workgroup, has seen anti-Asian hate transcend generations.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
Last February, a driver threw trash at his daughter while she was walking her dog near her home in Portland, Oregon.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
As the son of the late Jhoon Rhee \'96 the legendary taekwondo master who voluntarily taught his craft to hundreds of U.S. senators and representatives \'96 Jimmy Rhee recalled joining his father for training sessions as a teenager, even instructing President Joe Biden when Biden was a junior senator.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 Jhoon Rhee\'92s status didn\'92t shield Jimmy, who at 13 emigrated with his family from South Korea, from constant racial abuse and harassment growing up.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
Rhee said that stereotypes and ignorance \'96 including the notion of Asian Americans as \'93perpetual foreigners,\'94 regardless of how many generations their families have been in the U.S. \'96 contributes to the systemic inequality and hate that Asian Americans and Pacific Islanders face.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
Rhee said amending the issue will require significant educational investment to address.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
More than two-thirds of Asian Americans, and more than half of Pacific Islanders, have been asked where they are from, with the assumption that they aren\'92t from the U.S., according to a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://aapidata.com/blog/cross-racial-march2021-survey/"}}{\fldrslt \cf5 survey}} published by AAPI Data\'92s Karthick Ramakrishnan and Janelle Wong, who is also a professor of Asian American studies and political science at the University of Maryland, College Park.\cf0 \cb1 \
